The Fibonacci series starts with 0 and 1.
Each next number is the sum of the previous two numbers.
We use a loop to generate the series step by step.
steps
Start the program
Declare variables for terms and initial values
Take input from the user
Use a loop to generate the series
Calculate next term using sum of previous two
Print each term
End the program
Code
#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int n, i;
    int a = 0, b = 1, next;
    printf("Enter number of terms: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);

    printf("Fibonacci Series: ");

    for(i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        printf("%d ", a);
        next = a + b;
        a = b;
        b = next;
    }

    return 0;
}
